					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2250198#post-2803589</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2250198/scp-2659#post-2803589</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 28 Apr 2017 01:08:28 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>rknonchalance</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3068712</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>A good, unexpectedly short SCP that would make you think it'd have like a ton of exploration logs and agent com transcripts, but instead just leaves you out with a good wtf feeling. Kinda like that 'Wendy's demon flesh selling' SCP: Short but sweep, not overt horror or anything outright, it's you yourself instead that's forced to decide if that was really the case. (+1)</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
